OL,3,CMan who fell victim to paternity fraud
OL,4,Csays his 'life was ruined'
OL,6,FShe then asked for #300 towards a DNA
OL,7,Ftest, before sending him screenshots
OL,8,Fshowing there was a 99.9% probability
OL,9,Fhe was the father - claiming they were
OL,10,Ffrom company EasyDNA. The documents
OL,11,Fwere later confirmed to have been
OL,12,Fforged.
OL,14,FRyan is now calling for tougher laws
OL,15,Fon paternity fraud.
OL,17,FSpeaking on ITV's Good Morning
OL,18,FBritain, Ryan Hampson said: "This was
OL,19,Fsomething I was trying to get answers
OL,20,Fto for a very long time."
